THE EMPLOYER

The Brattle Group provides consulting and expert testimony in economics, finance, and regulation to corporations, law firms, and governments around the world. Our Principals are internationally recognized experts, and we have strong partnerships with leading academics and highly credentialed industry specialists around the world. For the fourth consecutive year, Brattle has been recognized in the Vault Consulting 50 as a top 10 consulting firm to work for and the highest among economic consulting firms. We have offices in Boston, MA; New York, NY; San Francisco, CA; Washington, DC; Toronto, ON; London, UK; Madrid, ES; Rome, IT; and Sydney, NSW.

Our New York office is conveniently located in the heart of Midtown Manhattan and accessible by multiple subway, train, and bus lines. 

THE POSITION

Are you an experienced administrative professional who is looking for a challenging new role?  Does a fast-paced, dynamic, collaborative, and fun culture interest you?  We have an exciting opportunity for someone who is looking to immerse him/herself in an environment where they are able and encouraged to contribute to many facets of our daily business. We are seeking someone with senior/executive level administrative experience (5+ years) to join the Business Support Services (BSS) team as a Senior Administrative Assistant in our New York office. The ideal candidate is motivated, flexible, and energized by providing top-notch client service.  

This full-time position directly supports the Director of Global Development as well as a Principal in the areas of coordination of communications, business development, project coordination and other various administrative responsibilities such as travel, expenses, and monthly billing. As a member of the BSS team, the Senior Administrative Assistant also shares responsibility in keeping the office environment tidy, well stocked and provides meeting coordination and set-up.  Additionally, this position reports to and takes day-to-day direction from the Director and Principal and secondarily reports to a BSS Manager. 

Some of the day-to-day responsibilities of this role include:

•	Prepares, revises, formats, and finalizes a wide variety of documents, including but not limited to testimony, reports, memoranda, articles, and presentations;
•	Transcribes formal dictations from Director to produce daily client and firm correspondence and manages voicemail and email inboxes as requested by Director; 
•	Acts as gatekeeper of Director's calendar, manages scheduling and ensures that Director is on schedule and appropriately prepared;
•	Manages Principal's and Director's day-to-day schedules/tasks, maximizing their time and efficiency; keep calendars updated; 
•	Updates and maintains client contact information and research and update current and potential client profiles, under the direction of Director and Senior Business Development Consultant;
•	Acts as point of contact for clients on behalf of project teams;
•	Manages project files, budgets, expenses, and monthly invoicing with project managers;
•	Prepares and submits expense reports on behalf of Director and Principal;
•	Coordinates all meetings including larger committee meetings as applicable; coordinates catering and meeting set up;
•	Coordinates all domestic and international business travel;
•	Performs copying, binding, faxing, scanning, and materials distribution as requested;
•	Interacts with other Corporate Services departments in the firm such as IT, Accounting, HR, and Marketing to ensure applicable information is communicated to the Director, Principal, and other BSS team members.

THE CANDIDATE

The position requires demonstrated organizational, time management, and communication skills as well as the ability to prioritize and execute numerous projects and deliverables.  The ideal candidate will be a self-directed individual who thrives in a dynamic environment that also provides autonomy and accountability.

Other requirements include: 

•	Bachelor's Degree preferred;
•	Requires a minimum of five (5) years of executive/senior-level administrative experience and project coordination, preferably in a law firm or other professional services firm;
•	Exceptional customer service skills and an eagerness to go above and beyond;
•	Willingness to work in a collegial team environment;
•	Advanced knowledge of Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, and Outlook is required;
•	Advanced proficiency formatting documents in Microsoft Word and minimum typing speed of 70 words per minute required;
•	Proficient use of MS Excel expected;
•	Database and budget tracking experience desired;
•	Ability to effectively manage time across all projects and deliverables;
•	Ability to exercise flexibility and appropriate judgment and to maintain confidentiality;
•	Acute attention to detail and ability to produce visually appealing and error-free work;
•	Ability to adapt easily to change;
•	Ability to work overtime, including night and weekend work as necessary;
•	Occasional travel.

THE PACKAGE

We offer a generous compensation and benefits package, including medical, dental, 401K/profit sharing, life and disability insurance, paid time off, and internal professional development and training programs, designed to reward success at all levels. Details regarding compensation will be based on the candidate's knowledge, skills, and experience. 

In order to be considered for this position, Please apply through the Careers section of our website (http://www.brattle.com/careers) by submitting a cover letter and resume. 

The Brattle Group is an equal opportunity employer: Minority/Female/Veteran/Disabled


